{"id":11579,"date":"2020-03-27T14:15:26","date_gmt":"2020-03-27T14:15:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/?p=11579"},"modified":"2020-03-27T14:15:28","modified_gmt":"2020-03-27T14:15:28","slug":"act4peace237-johnson-ebigwe-takes-over-douala","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/act4peace237-johnson-ebigwe-takes-over-douala\/","title":{"rendered":"ACT4PEACE237: JOHNSON EBIGWE TAKES OVER DOUALA"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>From January to February\n2020, our fellow for the Act4peace project carried different activities for\nthis campaign, in many areas of Douala.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The first activity was a Youth forum involving Youths from different organizations and religious backgrounds which informed them about the whole campaign. Johnson and his team also went to visit schools, introduced the Act4peace237 campaign to school authorities and booked sensitazation appointments at the General Assembly. A capacity building training session held with the prefects, was to make sure that they would be able to understand the concept and explain it to their population. The theme of their campaign was \u201cHate speech awareness and mitigation in the school milieu&#8221;. They covered many topics like the concept of Hate speech and Hate crimes; Hate speech and Human rights; the Pyramid of hate; Hate speech and social media.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200205-WA0037-1030x773.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11583\" width=\"749\" height=\"561\" srcset=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200205-WA0037-1030x773.jpg 1030w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200205-WA0037-744x558.jpg 744w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200205-WA0037-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200205-WA0037-705x529.jpg 705w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200205-WA0037.jpg 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 749px) 100vw, 749px\" \/><figcaption>One of the Assembly sensitization events<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0013.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11581\" width=\"761\" height=\"427\" srcset=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0013.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0013-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0013-705x397.jpg 705w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 761px) 100vw, 761px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0034.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11582\" srcset=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0034.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0034-744x419.jpg 744w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0034-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200124-WA0034-705x397.jpg 705w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In\naddition, an Act4peace237 party took place and brought together 20 influential\nartist and some very important persons in the Society and the IDPs. It was an\noccasion to do a Fund Raising to support them. Motor bikes riders also took\npart to an open-air campaign in street.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1030\" height=\"773\" src=\"https:\/\/defyhatenow.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG-20200203-WA0100-1-1030x773.jpg\